Many don't understand the XP DMA display bug.
I share it quite often.
But time and time again, the person is told that it will display the ide channel is in DMA, but the bug has it in PIO mode.
The fix is to set it to PIO, OK it then go back in to set it to DMA.
No reboot is needed, yet less than half can accomplish this task even with 100 word descriptions about the issue.
More words about this issue at http://www.microsoft.com/whdc/device/storage/IDE-DMA.mspx 2.
