Adding RAM.
While it's not loading that many 10M JPEG images, we did a real interesting test on our DVD rendering boxes.
There were 2 exact clones built for this with identical CPUs, boards, drives OS, settings and Video.
They diverged in that one had 512MB, the other had 1.0G RAM.
On the 6 hour render, the 1GB machine finished 5 minutes sooned.
We then moved a 512MB stick to the other machine and it finished 5 minutes sooner and the other machine went back to 6 hours.
For this application and setup, the payoff was so minuscule it was not funny.
